crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/cncr.29348">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25902916/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Use+of+neoadjuvant+chemotherapy+for+patients+with+stage+I+to+III+breast+cancer+in+the+United+States&amp;author=SS+Mougalian&amp;author=PR+Soulos&amp;author=BK+Killelea&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Cancer&amp;pages=2544-2552&amp;doi=10.1002%2Fcncr.29348&amp;pmid=25902916">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">4.</div><div id="r4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Vugts G, Maaskant-Braat AJ, Nieuwenhuijzen GA, Roumen RM, Luiten EJ, Voogd AC. Patterns of Care in the Administration of Neo-adjuvant Chemotherapy for Breast Cancer. A Population-Based Study. <em>Breast J</em> 2016;22(3):316–321.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/tbj.12568">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26945566/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Patterns+of+Care+in+the+Administration+of+Neo-adjuvant+Chemotherapy+for+Breast+Cancer.+A+Population-Based+Study&amp;author=G+Vugts&amp;author=AJ+Maaskant-Braat&amp;author=GA+Nieuwenhuijzen&amp;author=RM+Roumen&amp;author=EJ+Luiten&amp;author=AC+Voogd&amp;publication_year=2016&amp;journal=Breast+J&amp;pages=316-321&amp;doi=10.1111%2Ftbj.12568&amp;pmid=26945566">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Hurley J, Reis IM, Rodgers SE, et al. The use of neoadjuvant platinum-based chemotherapy in locally advanced breast cancer that is triple negative: retrospective analysis of 144 patients. <em>Breast Cancer Res Treat</em> 2013;138(3):783–794.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10549-013-2497-y">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23542956/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+use+of+neoadjuvant+platinum-based+chemotherapy+in+locally+advanced+breast+cancer+that+is+triple+negative%3A+retrospective+analysis+of+144+patients&amp;author=J+Hurley&amp;author=IM+Reis&amp;author=SE+Rodgers&amp;publication_year=2013&amp;journal=Breast+Cancer+Res+Treat&amp;pages=783-794&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs10549-013-2497-y&amp;pmid=23542956">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Heacock L, Lewin A, Ayoola A, et al. Dynamic Contrast-Enhanced MRI Evaluation of Pathologic Complete Response in Human Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor 2 (HER2)-Positive Breast Cancer After HER2-Targeted Therapy. <em>Acad Radiol</em> 2020;27(5):e87–e93.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.acra.2019.07.011">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31444111/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Dynamic+Contrast-Enhanced+MRI+Evaluation+of+Pathologic+Complete+Response+in+Human+Epidermal+Growth+Factor+Receptor+2+%28HER2%29-Positive+Breast+Cancer+After+HER2-Targeted+Therapy&amp;author=L+Heacock&amp;author=A+Lewin&amp;author=A+Ayoola&amp;publication_year=2020&amp;journal=Acad+Radiol&amp;pages=e87-e93&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.acra.2019.07.011&amp;pmid=31444111">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has=